The second China International Consumer Product Expo will be held in Haikou, south China's Hainan Province from July 26 to 30, with 30 days left till opening. The exhibition area will be expanded to 100,000 square meters, with more than 700 exhibiting companies and more than 1,300 exhibiting brands from 57 countries and regions, according to the Hainan International Economic Development Bureau. Japan, the U.S. and France are the top three exhibitors in terms of floor area. Meanwhile, 31 Chinese provinces, municipalities, and autonomous regions will showcase local consumer goods. A new national goods pavilion will be set up to highlight domestic high-quality products and time-honored brands. The initiative will provide a stage for Chinese companies to display and transact their products, and "go abroad".